				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\frac{1}{j} =\frac{1}{{j}_{\mathrm{k}}}+\frac{1}{{j}_{\mathrm{d}}}=\frac{1}{{j}_{\mathrm{k}}}+\frac{1}{B{\omega }^{1/2}}$$\end{document}Here j is the current density, jk and jd are the kinetic and diffusion-limiting current densities, respectively. The jd is a function of the rotation speed of the RDE (ω), while B is expressed by the following equation:8B=0.2nFD2/3ν-1/6c0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
